    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-01T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-01T14:00:00-05:00" n="388"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.014/84: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Izmir</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Izmir</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-01T21:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 1, 1943—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 2—12:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Germans on Samos have issued proclamation stating population will not be
                    oppressed; also that population must arrange own food problems.</p>
                <p>To date about 10,000 island refugees arrived Kusadasi and are being rapidly
                    evacuated to Alep as result of excellent cooperation Turkish, British, Greek
                    authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
